01:01:07.620 --> 01:01:11.300
There is one technical or
little trick we have to do,

01:01:11.300 --> 01:01:14.320
which is trivial, but
I want to mention it.

01:01:14.320 --> 01:01:23.730
So if you want to compare
directly with spin 1/2,

01:01:23.730 --> 01:01:32.690
we are now shifting
the ground state

01:01:32.690 --> 01:01:36.180
to half the
excitation frequency.

01:01:36.180 --> 01:01:39.690
In other words, just to make
the key analogy with the spin,

01:01:39.690 --> 01:01:42.710
usually we say for an electronic
transition, we start at 0,

01:01:42.710 --> 01:01:43.940
and we go up.

01:01:43.940 --> 01:01:47.550
But now we shift things
that the zero of energy

01:01:47.550 --> 01:01:50.610
is in the middle between the
ground and the excited state.

01:01:50.610 --> 01:01:53.740
And then, it looks like the
excited state, we spin up,

01:01:53.740 --> 01:01:56.430
the ground state, we spin down.

01:01:56.430 --> 01:02:10.000
So with that, our Hamiltonian
is now excited, excited,

01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:15.045
minus-- so all I've done
