01:03:16.090 --> 01:03:22.600
So therefore, for driving
an electronic transition

01:03:22.600 --> 01:03:30.660
with a laser beam,
we have actually

01:03:30.660 --> 01:03:42.691
spin Hamiltonian, which
has the standard form.

01:03:42.691 --> 01:03:44.440
So let me just write
it down, because it's

01:03:44.440 --> 01:03:46.620
an important result.

01:03:46.620 --> 01:03:51.220
The Hamiltonian for driving
and dipole transition

01:03:51.220 --> 01:03:58.260
with a linearly
polarized laser beam

01:03:58.260 --> 01:04:06.260
corresponds, or is identical,
to the Hamiltonian for spin 1/2,

01:04:06.260 --> 01:04:13.000
in a static magnetic field
along the Z direction,

01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:16.370
which causes a splitting
between spin up and spin down.

01:04:16.370 --> 01:04:24.030
And the splitting
is now omega eg

01:04:24.030 --> 01:04:28.550
plus a linearly
polarized oscillating

01:04:28.550 --> 01:04:45.449
field along the x direction.

01:04:52.790 --> 01:04:59.470
And you probably remember that
when we discussed the spin

01:04:59.470 --> 01:05:01.940
problem, what we
liked actually most

01:05:01.940 --> 01:05:06.500
was that we had a rotating
magnetic field, because it

01:05:06.500 --> 01:05:08.590
made everything simpler.

01:05:08.590 --> 01:05:16.200
And we are doing that
