01:07:21.150 --> 01:07:24.960
becomes now omega eg.

01:07:24.960 --> 01:07:30.970
And the co-rotating term
became stationary on resonance

01:07:30.970 --> 01:07:36.490
in this rotating frame, whereas
the counter-rotating term

01:07:36.490 --> 01:07:46.830
rotates at a very high frequency
in this frame at the Larmor

01:07:46.830 --> 01:07:47.330
frequency.

01:07:54.870 --> 01:08:05.140
So if this frequency, if
you fulfill the inequalities

01:08:05.140 --> 01:08:14.200
that the co-rotating term
is close to resonance,

01:08:14.200 --> 01:08:18.560
or in other words, we
are close to resonance,

01:08:18.560 --> 01:08:23.450
and we are not using an infinite
intensity of the laser beam,

01:08:23.450 --> 01:08:25.630
that we broaden everything
in co and counter

01:08:25.630 --> 01:08:28.310
rotating terms of
boson resonance.

01:08:28.310 --> 01:08:34.979
So if you fulfill
those two conditions,

01:08:34.979 --> 01:08:42.189
then we can neglect
the last term.

01:08:42.189 --> 01:08:46.671
And this is the rotating
wave approximation.

01:08:55.029 --> 01:08:57.359
So in other words,
