01:22:14.230 --> 01:22:16.300
But the take-home
message-- and what I

01:22:16.300 --> 01:22:20.470
really wanted to show you is
that we do have coherent Rabi

01:22:20.470 --> 01:22:22.170
oscillations.

01:22:22.170 --> 01:22:24.950
And by just performing
the integral

01:22:24.950 --> 01:22:29.190
over this broad
spectrum of the light,

01:22:29.190 --> 01:22:31.870
we lose the Rabi
oscillations, and we

01:22:31.870 --> 01:22:36.220
find rate equations,
Fermi's golden rule,

01:22:36.220 --> 01:22:40.620
and excitation probability
proportional to t.

01:22:40.620 --> 01:22:45.880
And we have done the transition
from coherent physics

01:22:45.880 --> 01:22:47.870
to irreversible physics.

01:22:47.870 --> 01:22:50.720
This is all hidden
in this one formula,

01:22:50.720 --> 01:22:54.230
but I want to fully explain
